  <h3 id="using-saildrone-autonomous-in-situ-data-for-satellite-validation-and-research-into-upper-ocean-physics-and-ecology-"><b> Using Saildrone autonomous in situ data for satellite validation and research into upper ocean physics and ecology </b></h3>

  <p> <b> Lead Investigator: Chelle Gentemann. </b> </p>

  <p> <b> Awarded by: Saildrone, Inc. and The Schmidt Family Foundation. </b> </p>

  <p>Publication:</p>

  <p>Gentemann, C.L., J.P. Scott, <b>P.L.F. Mazzini</b>, <b>C. Pianca</b>, S. Akella, P.J. Minnett, P. Cornillon, B. Fox-Kemper, I. CetiniÄ‡, T.M. Chin, J. Gomez-Valdes, J. Vazquez-Cuervo, V. Tsontos, L. Yu, R. Jenkins, S. De Halleux, D. Peacock, N. Cohen. Saildrone: adaptively sampling the marine environment. (2020). <i>Bulletin of the American Meteorological Society </i>. <a href="https://journals.ametsoc.org/doi/10.1175/BAMS-D-19-0015.1">[BAMS]</a></p>

